1.Refraction is the bending of light when it changes speed between two materials. 
2.Refraction takes place as light travels from air to water or vice versa.
3.Objects become either shorter or longer in dipping reflex. 
Refraction takes place as light travels from water to glass, which is why fish can be seen swimming in a circular path in the front of a mirror. 
Refraction takes place as light travels from air to water, as a swimmer can become shorter due to the increase in water density when they reach the surface.
4.Refraction takes place as light travels from air to water, as a swimmer can become longer when the water density decreases when they reach the bottom of a swim pool.
